description:
Someone is attacking friends and associates of the X-Men and it's up to Wolverine and his team to stop them. Meanwhile, newlywed Kyle learns the hard way that marrying Northstar also meant marrying his family, too bad Northstar's family is the X-Men!

Includes Alpha Flight #106 - The Walking Wounded
name: Welcome to the Family

description: Captain America and Black Widow face Lizard-Ock! Chased by a super-powered squad of killers, Cap and Widow take a trip through the multiverse! The stage is set for a final assault against Venemma Multiversal!
name: Raging Reptiles!

description:
Coerced by a criminal mastermind, Gambit is sent to the United Kingdom to heist the greatest weapon in the history of man: Excalibur.

How will Marvel's premiere thief manage to dupe his extortionist while also escaping with a clear name?

Guest-starring Pete Wisdom and MI13!
name: British Invasion

description:
The New Avengers era ends - not with a whimper - but with a extra-sized action-packed bang!

The last issue of New Avengers is actually all said and done: What is the future of the New Avengers? IS there a future? Find out right here.
name: The End

description: The robots of the Marvel Universe revolt! With the main team down, it's up to the Secret Avengers to stop Father's invasion and plague of robot evolution! But why has Captain Britain hurled mankind's only hope into the black heart of Earth-4680?
name: Synthetic Dawn

description:
DEMON IN THE ARMOR continues!

The mystery of ULTIMATE MANDARIN unfolds!

What secret of Tony's has turned WAR MACHINE against him?

Jarvis and Tony want to find out what the Mandarin was after when Carol Danvers stands in his door. She is angry because he wants to seduce her instead of taking her seriously. She tells him South Pacific Financial seems to be involved, so Tony goes to Hong Kong to investigate. He infiltrates South Pacific headquarters and finds clues that lead to the Mandarin but also point to his father. Before he can continue he is attacked by a security drone and retreats.

Tony dreams of his father, doing business with Asian companies. He wakes up and goes on trying to find out more about Mandarin despite Carol's reluctance. He asks Rhodey to join him on his quest which he wants to refuse. But then they are attacked by Stark drones.
name: Demon in the Armor, Part 2 of 4

description:
An All-New direction for the Ultimate X-Men!

Kitty tries to lead a new nation of mutants but someone close to her has different plans!

Brian (DMZ, STAR WARS, X-MEN) Wood's epic RESERVATION X arc begins here!
name: Reservation X; Part One

description:
THE FALL OUT OF MINIMUM CARNAGE IS HERE!

The wounds of Carnage still fresh, Flash Thompson confronts his past as a bully - and makes a momentous decision about his future!

Thony Silas returns with Cullen Bunn to Venom!
name: The Evil Inside Us All...

description: If the team can't defeat the Xavier from the United States of California...what will happen to Nightcrawler?
name: You Can't Go Home Again, Part 2

description: When Professor Simon vanished, the Air Force shanghaied the professor's son to Groom Lake to take over the job of babysitting the "problem" residents of Delta Hanger. Now Kirby Simon has to not only process that aliens actually exist, but the fact his father has been running a refugee camp for them under Area 51 without the government's knowledge and the acting up of the "Deltas" has been a cover for the alien's plan to save the professor from his captors. A plan that involves Kirby leading them...whether he's ready or not.
Special sneak previews of SUPERMAN #14, THE SAVAGE HAWKMAN #14, THE FLASH #14, RED LANTERNS #14, and TEEN TITANS #14! Plus, previews of all the DC comics in stores this week!
In the third issue of Lookouts, Voel's mysterious and inspiring origin story is told, the boys finally take on the troll without using any weapons, and Dore bites off more than he can chew.
name: Riddle, Part 3; Brewell's Charm

description: Return to the world of MEMORIAL in "Imaginary Fiends," an all new digital-only 9 part series! The fantasies and fears that seem so real to children are often forgotten in adulthood. But after the events of the first Memorial miniseries, forgotten memories are being recovered all over the world. Can those lost fears and fantasies be far behind? Brought to you by Chris Roberson (EDISON REX, iZOMBIE), Rich Ellis (STARS BELOW, TWILIGHT ZONE), and Grace Allison (WANDER). Chapter 4 of 9.

Return to the world of MEMORIAL in "Imaginary Fiends," an all new digital-only 9 part series! The fantasies and fears that seem so real to children are often forgotten in adulthood. But after the events of the first Memorial miniseries, forgotten memories are being recovered all over the world. Can those lost fears and fantasies be far behind? Brought to you by Chris Roberson (EDISON REX, iZOMBIE), Rich Ellis (STARS BELOW, TWILIGHT ZONE), and Grace Allison (WANDER). Chapter 5 of 9.

In this issue we take a break from the main story arc of Mumbai Confidential for two interludes. Our first interlude features a man who loves Mumbai with all his heart... but dislikes her other suitors. The second follows the inner monologue of a hitman as he prepares for his next job. Also includes an introduction by author Arnab Ray.
PRESENT TENSE PART TWO: We continue to peek into the possible future of the WAYWARD SONS universe!

When Professor Simon vanished, the Air Force shanghaied the professor's son to Groom Lake to take over the job of babysitting the "problem" residents of Delta Hanger. Now Kirby Simon has to not only process that aliens actually exist, but the fact his father has been running a refugee camp for them under Area 51 without the government's knowledge and the acting up of the "Deltas" has been a cover for the alien's plan to save the professor from his captors. A plan that involves Kirby leading them - whether he's ready or not!

It's the world's first comic-book/newspaper strip crossover event, as Spider-Man teams up with fan-favorite X-Man and Avenger the Beast! When the Brand Corporation announces it has discovered the secret of mutation, the two heroes investigate - but run smack-dab into the Hobgoblin! Watch the action unfold in the pages of the comic book AND the daily Spider-Man newspaper strip! Plus, a classic Marvel Team-Up from yesteryear, as Spidey and the Beast battle the dual threat of Killer Shrike and the Modular Man! Collecting SPIDER-MAN: THE MUTANT AGENDA #0-3 and MARVEL TEAM-UP (1972) #90.
name: TPB

description:
SPIDER-MAN FIGHTS A DRAGON!

And then! Spider-Man is outmatched when he takes on a new team of seasoned villains!

No need to wait for another episode of Disney XD's hit TV show with this comic in your hands!
name: Dragon Me Down!; Four Seasons

description: Things get hairy in Vegas where rival girl gangs scuffle in the desert and The King and her women wreak havoc. That's not the only problem: all the zombies that used to be men line the outskirts of town.

Women in Mexican wrestling masks and ultra-violent female Elvis impersonators dot the desert around Las Vegas, if only to feud with one another over the local bootlegging industry and battle man-zombies.
The King's plans come to fruition and the truth behind Megan's betrayal of the Bombshells unfurls as everyone fights to control they city.
The King continues her sinister game of chess with The Black Cherry Bombshells as her pieces and the fate of female humanity in the balance.
The girl gangs of Las Vegas continue to scrap with the Black Cherry Bombshells for the remains of humanity under the machinations of The King.
Megan sets off to rescue Ms. Jackson from The King, while Regina goes on a quest to find herself. Special pages drawn by SuperTron creator Sheldon Vella.
Regina completes her personal quests and charges back into The King's base to defeat her and reunite the Black Cherry Bombshells.
It all comes to a knock-down, knuckle-bashing battle between The King and the Black Cherry Bombshells. Who will be left standing?

Who is the Terrible TOYMAN? What does he want, anyway? Where does he get all those cool toys?

Can't a Super Family have a Tooth Fairy Party in peace?

Better save your receipts, because these toys are about to malfunction!

Collects Spawn issues 6-9 and 11.

The mob of Spawns city send a super villain, Overtkill, on to his tail kill him.

The classic "Spawn-story" written by Alan Moore, in which Billy Kincaids destiny is revealed.

Another classic Spawn issue, the one written by Neil Gaiman, which tells about a medieval Spawn, and a woman called Angel.

And a story written by Frank Miller.
name: Spawn Book 2: Dark discoveries
De Kat gaat er op af

description: Re-visiting the launch of the ongoing series that kick-started a brand new era for the TRANSFORMERS saga! The Earth has been rebuilt, the Autobots are in hiding, and fans will want to see where it all started!

Abner joins an all ladies' wrestling league and he and his new bride Daisy Mae welcome into the world their very own bundle of joy, "Mysterious" Yokum. This nineteenth volume reprints the 1953 daily strips and includes an illustrated introduction by Tom Andrae detailing the history of the long-lost Fearless Fosdick television series.
name: The Stupefying Birth of "Mysterious" Yokum

description:
This issue includes Justice League #5

Now, with the teenaged powerhouse Cyborg at their side, this group of individual heroes must somehow put their differences aside to face the terror of Darkseid!
name: Justice League Parte Cinco

description:
this issue includes Batman: Arkham City #4

The gates swing shut on Arkham City, trapping small-time criminals and deadly Super-Villains behind its walls. As the prisoners struggle for survival, a rogue unit of Mayor Sharp's security force hunts down rival gang bosses The Joker and Two-Face. Not only must Batman save the lives of his greatest foes, he's got to fight his way through an army to do it!
name: Batman Arkham City #4: Una noche en el pueblo

description:
This isssue includes Green Lantern #5

The conclusion to Sinestro and Hal Jordan's invasion of the planet Korugar! Can these two enemies cooperate long enough to liberate the world from the tyranny of the Sinestro Corps?
name: Sinestro Parte Cinco

description: This issue includes Aquaman #5
name: Perdido

description: This issue includes The Flash #5
This issue includes Wonder Woman #5
name: Lourdes

description:
The digital-first saga continues in the print debut of these Beyond adventures!

Witness the last stand of the Justice League against Kobra in this storyline’s cataclysmic conclusion!

Superman settles into his new civilian identity as a ghost from his past appears to torment his future!

“10,000 Clowns” continues as Batman and his allies desperately try to stop the assault on Gotham City!
name: Konstriction: Hell on Earth & The Mortal Coil; 10,000 Clowns: Lights of Gotham; Man of Steel

description: Bruce Wayne has begun to accept his new reality, but that comes at a price. Will Batman emerge from the Scarecrow's plot a broken man, or a stronger hero than before? "Dreaming He is a Butterfly" part 2 of 2.
name: Dreaming He is a Butterfly, Part 2 of 2
